[thinking] I'm considering whether to use nested helper classes inside a single Java file, which could reduce the number of files. However, the test class file should remain separate since the helpers aren't tests. It seems that using top-level helper classes might be clearer, even though there's an idea about avoiding `$` in class names—maybe that doesn't apply to helpers. I also wonder if using assertj instead of JUnit would be better, especially since Scala is currently using JUnit. Time to think through these options!
